Test Cases for Create Collection Functionality
Test Case ID	Test Case Description	Test Steps	Expected Result
TC_01	Verify that a user can create a new collection	1. Click on the "Create Collection" button.
2. Enter a Collection Name.
3. Select files from the file list.
4. Enter a description (optional).
5. Click "Create".	1. The "Create Collection" form should open.
2. Users should be able to enter a name, select multiple files, and enter a description.
3. The new collection should be successfully created and visible in the list.
TC_02	Verify that a collection cannot be created without a name	1. Click on "Create Collection".
2. Do not enter a Collection Name.
3. Select files and click "Create".	A validation message should appear: "Collection name is required."
TC_03	Verify that a collection cannot be created without selecting files	1. Click on "Create Collection".
2. Enter a Collection Name.
3. Do not select any files.
4. Click "Create".	A validation message should appear: "Please select at least one file."
TC_04	Verify the file selection dropdown functionality	1. Click on the file dropdown.
2. Search for a specific file.
3. Select a file from the list.	1. The dropdown should display all available files.
2. The user should be able to search for files.
3. The selected file should be added to the collection.
TC_05	Verify that a collection can be created with a description	1. Click "Create Collection".
2. Enter a Collection Name.
3. Select one or more files.
4. Enter a description.
5. Click "Create".	1. The collection should be created successfully.
2. The description should be saved and visible when viewing the collection.
TC_06	Verify the behavior when trying to create a duplicate collection name	1. Create a collection with a specific name.
2. Try to create another collection with the same name and files.
3. Click "Create".	The system should either allow duplicates or display an error message like "Collection name already exists."
TC_07	Verify the "Cancel" button functionality	1. Click "Create Collection".
2. Enter a name, select files, and enter a description.
3. Click "Cancel".	1. The collection creation form should close.
2. No collection should be created.
TC_08	Verify UI elements on the Create Collection page	1. Open the Create Collection page.
2. Check for all elements: Collection Name, File selection, Description input, Create & Cancel buttons.	1. All UI elements should be present and functional.
2. Buttons should be clickable.
